quran[32]{c,v,t,f}:
86,1,"By the heaven, and the night-visitor,"
86,2,"what do you know what the night-visitor is?"
86,3,"It is the piercing star."
86,4,"There is no living being but there is a protector over it. {1}",footnotes:1:A Guardian: Allah Almighty Himself
86,5,"So let man consider of what he was created. {1}",footnotes:1:After inviting man to ponder over the heavens
86,6,"He was created of a gushing fluid,"
86,7,"emanating from between the loins and the ribs. {1}",footnotes:1:“A fluid gushing forth” means ejaculation of semen (maain) carrying the sperm (nutfa)
86,8,"Surely He (the Creator) has the power to bring him back (to life). {1}",footnotes:1:Sulb is the backbone (vertebral column) and taraib the ribs. There are 12 pairs of ribs. Of them
86,9,"On the Day when man's deepest secrets shall be put to the test {1}",footnotes:1:That is
86,10,"he shall have no power, and no helper."
86,11,"By the heaven with its recurring cycle of rain, {1}",footnotes:1:The hidden secrets: the acts of every person which remained a secret to the world as well as those affairs which came before the world only in their apparent form
86,12,"and by the earth ever bursting with verdure,"
86,13,"this (Qur'an) is surely a decisive Word,"
86,14,"not a flippant jest. {1}",footnotes:1:The words dhat ar-raje have been used for the sky. Literally raje means to return
86,15,"They are devising a guile, {1}",footnotes:1:That is
86,16,"and I too am devising a guile. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
86,17,"So leave the unbelievers to themselves; respite them awhile. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
87,1,"Glorify the name of your Lord, the Most High, {1}",footnotes:1:Literally: “Glorify the name of your Lord
87,2,"Who created all things and fashioned them in good proportion; {1}",footnotes:1:That is
87,3,"Who determined {1} and guided them, {2}",footnotes:1:That is
87,4,"Who brought forth the pasture, {1}",footnotes:1:The word maraa as used in the text means the fodder for animals but the context shows that here it does not imply mere fodder but every kind of vegetation that grows out of the soil.
87,5,"and then made it into a blackish straw. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
(Surah Al-Hadid, Ayat 20).
87,6,"We shall make you recite and then you will not forget, {1}",footnotes:1:Hakim has related from Saad bin Abi Waqqas and Ibn Marduyah from Abdullah bin Abbas that the Prophet (peace be upon him) repeated the words of the Quran for fear lest he should forget them. Mujahid and Kalbi say that even before Gabriel finished recitation of the revelation the Prophet (peace be upon him) would start repeating the initial verses lest he should forget them. On this very basis Allah assured him that he should listen quietly when the revelation was coming down
87,7,"except what Allah should wish. {1} He knows all that is manifest and all that is hidden. {2}",footnotes:1:This sentence can have two meanings: First
87,8,"We shall ease you to follow the way of Ease."
87,9,"So render good counsel if good counsel will avail. {1}",footnotes:1:Generally
87,10,"He who fears (Allah) shall heed it, {1}",footnotes:1:That is
87,11,"but the wretched will turn away from it."
87,12,"He will be cast into the Great Fire."
87,13,"Then he will neither die in it, nor live. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
87,14,"He who purified himself shall prosper, {1}",footnotes:1:Who purified himself: Who affirmed the faith giving up disbelief and polytheism
87,15,"remembering his Lord's name {1} and praying. {2}",footnotes:1:To remember Allah signifies His remembrance in the heart as well as with the tongue.That is
